You are writing the TOOLS layer. Tools are thin async wrappers around external APIs. They never contain business logic.

## Mandatory tool contract
- MUST extend `BaseTool` from `backend/tools/base_tool.py`
- MUST implement `async def call(self, **kwargs) -> Optional[dict]`
- MUST return `None` on ANY failure — never raise to caller
- MUST include in every return dict: `source_url: str`, `fetched_at: str (ISO)`, `tool_name: str`
- MUST use `@cached_call(ttl=300)` decorator for identical inputs

## Retry & rate limit rules
- Exponential backoff: 3 retries, base delay 1s, multiplier 2x
- Hard timeout per call: 8 seconds
- Log every failure with: tool name, error type, input hash (not raw input)

## Tool-specific rules

### ip_lookup.py
- Primary: ipapi.co — Fallback: ip-api.com
- If org/isp contains AWS, GCP, Azure, Cloudflare, DigitalOcean → set company_name to None
- Return: `{company_name, country, city, isp, org, confidence}`

### web_search.py
- Use Tavily API — key from `settings.TAVILY_API_KEY`
- Max 5 results, filter out: reddit.com, quora.com, pinterest.com
- Always include result rank and domain in returned dict

### scraper.py
- Timeout 8s hard limit using `asyncio.wait_for`
- Extract: title, meta_description, first 2000 chars visible text, all script src attrs
- Script srcs are used for tech stack detection — never discard them

### enrichment_apis.py
- Try Clearbit → Apollo → LLM fallback in that order
- Never expose raw API response shapes — always normalize to CompanyProfile-compatible dict

## Forbidden in tools/
- No LLM calls — tools are pure I/O, reasoning belongs in agents
- No domain logic, scoring, or inference
